K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mThought for \u001b[1m52s\u001b[22m, ran \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \r\u001b[2B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mStrong scout complete. The repo already has prior cloud-model reviews (\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mfable-proposals.md\u001b[39m,\u001b[94G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mollama-minimax-proposals.md\u001b[39m,\u001b[123G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mollama-gdm-proposals.md\u001b[39m)\u001b[148Gplus\u001b[153Gan\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mARCHITECTURE-REVIEW-TODO.md\u001b[31G\u001b[39mwith\u001b[36G8\u001b[38Gitems.\u001b[45GSo\u001b[48GGLM-5.2's\u001b[58Greview\u001b[65Gshould\u001b[72G(a)\u001b[76Gfocus\u001b[82Gon\u001b[85Gthe\u001b[89G\u001b[1mOllama embedding integration\u001b[118G\u001b[22m(the\u001b[123Glive\u001b[128Gfailure\u001b[136GI\u001b[138Gsaw\u001b[142G—\u001b[144Gvector\u001b[151Gsearch\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3Gsilently off — is\u001b[21Gthe he\u001b[28Gdline), and (b) build on / delta against the prior reviews rather than duplicate\u001b[112Gm.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BI'll fan out\u001b[16Ga\u001b[18Greview\u001b[25Gworkflow:\u001b[35G9\u001b[37Gdimensions\u001b[48G→\u001b[50Gadversarial\u001b[62Gverification\u001b[75Gof\u001b[78Geach\u001b[83Gactionable\u001b[94Gfinding\u001b[102G→\u001b[104GI\u001b[106Gauthor\u001b[113Gthe\u001b[117Gfinal\u001b[123G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mREVIEW-ollama-glm-5.2.txt\u001b[149G\u001b[39mfrom\u001b[154Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bconfirmed\u001b[13Gevidence.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;78;186;101m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39m\u001b[1mWorkflow\u001b[22m(GLM-5.2\u001b[20Greview\u001b[27Gof\u001b[30Gthe\u001b[34Gtotal-recall\u001b[47Gplugin,\u001b[55GOllama-integration\u001b[74Gangle,\u001b[81Gwith\u001b[86Gadversarial\u001b[98Gverification)\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m  ⎿  Running in background · \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m/workflows\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m to monitor and save\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m \u001b[3G\u001b[39mThinking\u001b[12Gfor\u001b[16G\u001b[1m21s\u001b[22m…\u001b[21G\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m  ⎿  \u001b[39m\u001b[2m\u001b[3mThe workflow is running in the background. While it runs, let me read the existing proposals files myself so I can author a good synthesis. Actually, the \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m   \u001b[2m\u001b[3mworkflow's prior-reviews-delta agent is reading those. But I want to be in the loop for the final authoring. Let me read the key files myself in parallel — \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m   \u001b[2m\u001b[3mspecifically the Ollama proposals (since the output is \"REVIEW-ollama-glm-5.2.txt\") and the embeddings.ts source, so my synthesis is grounded and not just \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Brelaying agent output. Let me read in parallel: embeddings.ts, vectorStore.ts, and the headers of the two ollama proposals files. This keeps me grounded while \r\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m \u001b[3G   \u001b[2m\u001b[3mthe workflow runs. Actually, the workflow will take a while (9 review agents + ~40 verify agents, concurrency 16). Let me read the core Ollama files myself now\r\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m     \u001b[2m\u001b[3mso I can independently sanity-check the agents' findings.\u001b[23m\u001b[22m\u001b[45;1H\u001b[39;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
