[1107.514257, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\u001b[7G\"summary\":\u001b[18G\"GLM-5.2\u001b[27Greview\u001b[34Gof\u001b[37Gthe\u001b[41Gtotal-recall\u001b[54Gplugin,\u001b[62GOllama-integration\u001b[81Gangle,\u001b[88Gwith\u001b[93Gadversarial\u001b[105Gverification\",\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3G    \"agentCount\": 51,\r\u001b[1B      \"logs\": [\u001b[K\r\u001b[4C\u001b[1B \u001b[9G\"Review\u001b[17Gcomplete:\u001b[27G37\u001b[30Gconfirmed,\u001b[41G3\u001b[43Gpartial,\u001b[52G2\u001b[54Grefuted,\u001b[63G23\u001b[66Gstrengths\u001b[76Gacross\u001b[83G9\u001b[85Gdimensions.\"\r\u001b[6C\u001b[1B],\u001b[K\r\u001b[7C\u001b[1Bresult\": {\u001b[K\r\u001b[6C\u001b[1B  \"dimensions\":\u001b[23G[\r\u001b[8C\u001b[1B  {\u001b[K\r\u001b[6C\u001b[1B  \u001b[13G\"dimension\":\u001b[26G\"ollama-embeddings\",\r\u001b[6C\u001b[1B      \"summary\":\u001b[24G\"The\u001b[29GOllama\u001b[36Gembedding\u001b[46Gpath\u001b[51Gis\u001b[54Ga\u001b[56Gsingle\u001b[63Ghardcoded-style\u001b[79GHTTP\u001b[84GPOST\u001b[89Gto\u001b[92Gthe\u001b[96Glegacy\u001b[103G/api/embeddings\u001b[119Gendpoint\u001b[128Gwith\u001b[133Ga\u001b[135Gconfigurable\u001b[148Gmodel\r\u001b[4C\u001b[1B(default bge-m3),\u001b[23GUR\r\u001b[10C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;78;186;101m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mDynamic\u001b[11Gworkflow \"GLM-5.2 review of the total-recall\u001b[56Gplugin,\u001b[64GOllama-integration\u001b[83Gangle,\u001b[90Gwith\u001b[95Gadversarial\u001b[107Gverification\"\u001b[121Gcompleted\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m · 13m 3s\r\u001b[12C\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mThought for \u001b[1m3s\u001b[22m \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mWorkflow done: 51 agents,\u001b[29G\u001b[1m37 confirmed\u001b[22m,\u001b[43G3 p\u001b[47Grtial, 2\u001b[56Grefuted, 23 stre\u001b[73Ggths. The\u001b[83G\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mconfirmed\u001b[39m/\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mpartial\u001b[39m \u001b[103Gr\u001b[105Gys a\u001b[110Ge \u001b[113Gn \u001b[116Ghe truncat\u001b[127Gd middle of the\u001b[143Gnotification.\u001b[157GLet\u001b[161Gme\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bextract\u001b[11Gthem\u001b[16Gfrom\u001b[21Gthe\u001b[25Gfull\u001b[30Goutput\u001b[37Gfile.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mThought for \u001b[1m4s\u001b[22m, ran \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThe parse retu\u001b[18Gned empty —\u001b[30Gthe file structure\u001b[49Gisn't\u001b[55Ga\u001b[57Gsingle\u001b[64Gclean\u001b[70GJSON.\u001b[76GLet\u001b[80Gme\u001b[83Ginspect\u001b[91Gits\u001b[95Gactual\u001b[102Gshape.\r\u001b[2B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThinking for \u001b[1m5s\u001b[22m, running \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command…\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m  ⎿  \u001b[39m\u001b[2m\u001b[3mThe file is a clean JSON: \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m{ summary, agentCount, logs, result: { dimensions, confirmed, partial, refutedSummary, strengths, counts } }\u001b[39m. Brace count is 217 vs \r\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m \u001b[3G   \u001b[2m\u001b[3m214 — slightly mismatched, but the file starts with \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m{\u001b[39m and ends with \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m}\u001b[39m. My earlier parse failed because... actually the file IS valid-ish JSON wrapped in \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;177;185;249mresult\u001b[39m. My python \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mjson.loads(raw[start:])\u001b[39m should have worked. But it returned empty counts. Wait — maybe the parse actually failed silently? No, json.loads \r\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m \u001b[3G   \u001b[2m\u001b[3mwould raise on error. It returned an object but \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj.get('counts')\u001b[39m was empty and \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj.get('dimensions')\u001b[39m empty — because those are under \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj['result']\u001b[39m, not \r\u001b[1B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m     \u001b[2m\u001b[3mtop-level! I queried \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj.get('counts')\u001b[39m and \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj.get('dimensions')\u001b[39m but they're inside \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj['result']\u001b[39m. That's the bug in my script. Let me fix: use \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mobj['result']\u001b[39m. \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1BThe brace mismatch (217 vs 214) might mean the JSON is slightly malformed (3 extra opening braces — maybe from regex content in findings). But json.loads \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Bsucceeded in my first script (it didn't throw), so it must be balanced enough... actually if it parsed, braces were balanced. The grep -o '{' counts 217 vs '}'\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B214 — but grep -o counts occurrences in the raw text including those inside strings (like code samples with \u001b[38;2;177;185;249m{\u001b[39m in evidence fields). So the JSON itself is \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Bbalanced; the discrepancy is from braces inside string values. Fine. Let me re-run with the correct path: obj['result'].\r\u001b[43C\u001b[2B\u001b[23m\u001b[22m\u001b[38;2;153;153;153mought for 3s)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[141C\u001b[2B \u001b[38;2;153;153;153m7\u001b[39m\u001b[45;1H\u001b[39;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
